{"questionId":"32385516","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>For extra support, Gaurika decides to attach a rope, with length <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math> , to the tent at a point, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi></math> , on the edge <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>AT</mi></math>.</p>\n<p>The rope will be fixed to the ground at point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Y</mi></math>, such that:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>the rope, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mi>XY</mi></mfenced></math>, is straight</li>\n<li>points <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Y</mi></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math> lie on a straight line</li>\n<li>\n<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Y</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>35</mn><mo>°</mo></math>.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>This is shown in the diagrams.<br><br></p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/d23fb3bacbf1c27960656e24fb4d36d19a698258.png\" width=\"592\" height=\"253\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>the volume of the tent.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3923</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>×</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>74954</mn><mo>…</mo></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>52</mn><mo> </mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>52470</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>)</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note</strong>: Units must be seen.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"32385516","referenceCode":"24N.2.AHL.TZ0.4bii","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"the volume of the tent.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.1—3d space, volume, angles, midpoints","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.2—2d and 3d trig"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":3}
